gomodel:SYNGO_679  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: - Overexpression of LRRTM4-Fc decreases excitatory synapse density in DIV14 hippocampal neurons (Figure 5, Myc-tagged LRRTM4).\n- Synaptogenic activity of LRRTM4 in HEK cells (Figures 6A-6D). (HEK cells, Myc-tagged LRRTM4).\n- LRRTM4 knockdown significantly decreases the density of dendritic protrusions in vivo and reduced synaptic currents (ctx neurons, shRNA KD).\n\n24/5/2017 Pim\n- All points to a role of LRRTM4 in synapse assembly (aka synapse formation) via a trans-synaptic interaction with GPC4.. Experimental description: Fig.5 \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from P0 Long-Evans **rats** (Charles River) \"\nFig.5+6 (Suppl.Info.): \"HEK293T cells were transfected with myc-tagged mouse LRRTM4\" The overexpression construct is of **mouse** species.\nFig.8: \"Embryonic day 15.5 mouse embryos were electroporated with control or shLRRTM4 plasmids, \"\n\n24/5/2017 Pim\nBecause of the species of the OE construct and the experiments in mice the annotated species should be mouse." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-05-26" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_679" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

